HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 413
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Sage Arnold, 2025 Top
Ten Senior of Hampshire Unit School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Sage Arnold is one such exceptional student, who was recently named a
Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Hampshire Unit School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Arnold has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Sage Arnold has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including HOSA, FCA, and basketball; and
WHEREAS, additionally, during her tenure at Hampshire Unit School, she has given
generously of her time, serving as a teacher's assistant and a concession stand attendant; and
WHEREAS, Sage Arnold's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for her future success at the Tennessee College of Applied Technology Hohenwald, where she
will study to become a surgical technologist; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Arnold's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her parents, Norisa and Dwight Arnold, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Sage Arnold's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
